<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10045175747034218852">Jon J. Muth is an American comic artist. His works include J. M. DeMatteis&apos; graphic novel <i>Moonshadow</i>, Neil Gaiman&apos;s <i>The Sandman: The Wake</i> (along with Michael Zulli, Charles Vess), Mike Cary&apos;s <i>Lucifer: Nirvana</i> and <i>Swamp Thing: Roots</i>. Muth has gone on to an award-winning career as a children&apos;s book writer and illustrator. He received a Gold Medal from the Society of Illustrators for his illustration</span>
  <span id="freeText10045175747034218852" style="display:none">Jon J. Muth is an American comic artist. His works include J. M. DeMatteis' graphic novel <i>Moonshadow</i>, Neil Gaiman's <i>The Sandman: The Wake</i> (along with Michael Zulli, Charles Vess), Mike Cary's <i>Lucifer: Nirvana</i> and <i>Swamp Thing: Roots</i>. Muth has gone on to an award-winning career as a children's book writer and illustrator. He received a Gold Medal from the Society of Illustrators for his illustrations in <i>Come On, Rain!</i> by Karen Hesse.<br /><br />He has also created a version of the Stone soup fable set in China.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10045175747034218852" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

